Echani prefer elegant design to brute force.  The Maktites learned this when their stores of thermal weapons were rendered ineffective by simple changes in the Echani light armor.

There are a variety of different kinds of armor intended to defend against the harsh enviroments of space, deflect the impact of blaster bolts and protect versus all types of damage that can be found on a battlefield. These suits are usually built in with a personal shield generator.

The E-11 blaster rifle is a blaster rifle manufactured by BlasTech Industries during the Galactic Civil War. It is the standard blaster rifle of the Imperial stormtroopers. A powerful, light and compact weapon, the E-11 is used widely through the galaxy.

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.

Power paks or power cells provide energy for many vehicles, and small blaster weapons. Most power cells contain concentrated amounts of gases that, when heated, form plasma. In small blasters, power cells are used to create blaster bolts that are not nearly as powerful as blasters using a combination of magazines containing gases (that after being heated would change into plasma) and proper Blaster power packs. A small power cell could be used to power a prosthetic without the need for recharging.

Heff's Souvenirs is a location in Mos Eisley on Tatooine. It is generally considered a junk shop. It sold anything that is broken, damaged or completely obsolete. It also had a few souvenirs that are related to Tatooine such as a glazed Womp Rat. The place is owned by the Sullustan Moplin Jarron who bought the shop after Heff was killed in an incident involving bounty hunters a few years ago.
Spaceport Speeders is a speeder shop in Mos Eisley. The proprietor of Spaceport Speeders is an Arcona called Unut Poll. Wioslea the Vuvrian also works there.

Tamoss, like his partner Daushoroc, is an Eirrauc and a former slave of the Galactic Empire. After escaping together, and settling some other escaped slaves on a safeworld, they became dealers in gems, curiosities, and rare artifacts. In 0 BBY, they arrived on Tatooine to search for the wreck of the Athallian Messenger. The two traders had to make peace with a tribe of Tusken Raiders just to get to the part of the desert the wrecked hull was said to be.

The Spaceport Hotel is a hotel established in Mos Eisley on the world of Tatooine; it has a reputation as being somewhat less then mediocre. The hotel boasts forty rooms available, and each room cost approximately fifteen credits for a one-night stay. The only employee known to work there is a Sullustan.

Kayson's Weapons Shop is based in Mos Eisley and is a distributor of firearms. It is probably the best weapons shop in the city and is run by Kayson, a grizzled alien, who is also very adept at obtaining weapons on the black market.

Lup's General Store was a location in Mos Eisley on Tatooine. It is owned by two Shistavanen, Kal Lup and Tar Lup. The store is located near Outer Curved Street near Spaceport Speeders. The Lups sells everything from provisions to supplies and machinery.
This is used by the shop owner to set what the shop has for sale.

"And folks come from lightyears away just to sink their teeth, fangs, or whatever into the best banthaburger this side of the Cheenee Rift!"

Gep's Grill is a stall in the market place where grilled Dewback and Bantha meat is offered at fair prices. It is currently owned by two Whiphids, Fillin Ta and Norun Gep. The menu is simple, but adequate for the people who visited the place. Rumors have it that the owners have been forced to temporarily close their Grill and quickly leave to other planets under the guise of seeking new sources of meat.
